{
  "doc_id": "17639",
  "text": "Cytotoxicity was evaluated using the 3-(4,5-dimethylthiazol-2-yl)-2,5-diphenyltetrazolium bromide (MTT) colorimetric assay (Sigma-Aldrich) [CITATION_1] . The cells were incubated with Cop at different concentrations associated or not with LPS for 24 h. The supernatants were removed and the cells were incubated with 5% MTT in RPMI-c for 4 h. Then, 150 L of DMSO was added to each well and maintained at room temperature until complete solubilization of the precipitated. Absorbance was measured at 570 nm with a spectrophotometer (mQuanti, Bio-Tek Instruments, Inc., Winooski, VT) and was directly proportional to cell viability.",
